1. MultiContainer Pod (Side car)

  => Pods is a smallest unit that can be deployed and managed by k8s. Its contain containers with network, resource like cpu. In other words, if you need to run a single container in Kubernetes, then you need to create a Pod for that container

  => No High avalibility
  => No Scalibility
  => No Load spin accross the containers inside the pod.
  => ip not assign to every container inside the pod. they have only single ip-address.
  => Use case of more than containers inside the single pod. => Side car: when application  required helper to get data.

 IQ) Use Cases for Kubernetes Multi-Container Pods
    The primary purpose of a multi-container Pod is to support primary container application.

     a) Sidecar container : "help" the main container.
        Examples:
           1. Some examples include log or data change watchers, monitoring adapters, and so on.
           2. Sidecar container is a file or data loader that generates data for the main container.

     b) Proxies, bridges, and adapters connect the main container with the external world.


URL => https://www.mirantis.com/blog/multi-container-pods-and-container-communication-in-kubernetes/
    => https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/kubernetes-creating-multiple-container-in-a-pod/

example-1
=========
cat > pod.yml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  creationTimestamp: null
  labels:
    run: demo
  name: demo
spec:
  containers:
  - image: nginx
    name: app
  - image: redis
    name: db

root@kube-master:~# kubectl get pod -o wide
NAME   READY   STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE     IP               NODE         NOMINATED NODE   READINESS GATES
demo   2/2     Running   0          3m24s   172.24.186.114   kube-node2   <none>           <none>

root@kube-master:~# kubectl -it exec demo -c app bash
root@kube-master:~# kubectl -it exec demo -c db bash


   		Note: => Both containers will talk through loopback(127.0.0.1) ip-address with different port.
              => Both containers always run on same node with same ip address.
              => On this type of pods. Network and volume are shared by default for each other.
              => when container required helper, then we need to create multiContainer like sidecar in single pod.



2. Init Container : It verify the conditions (like application check, port check), before start application and once it complete his work. it will delete. (work like precheck before application)e
Example:1

root@kube-master:~# cat init-container.yml 
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: init-demo
spec:
  containers:
  - name: nginx
    image: nginx
    ports:
    - containerPort: 80
    volumeMounts:
    - name: workdir
      mountPath: /usr/share/nginx/html
  # These containers are run during pod initialization
  initContainers:
  - name: install
    image: busybox:1.28
    command:
    - wget
    - "-O"
    - "/work-dir/index.html"
    - http://info.cern.ch
    volumeMounts:
    - name: workdir
      mountPath: "/work-dir"
  dnsPolicy: Default
  volumes:
  - name: workdir
    emptyDir: {}

